<TITLE> Security, police freedom top agenda: Sohel Taj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com)  State minister for home Tanjim Ahmed has said the government will be strict to maintain security, and allow the police to operate independently. "A joint task force will be formed to uproot militancy," he said in an interview with a private TV station. "After taking over responsibilities, I had a meeting with senior police officials and they have been told to work professionally and independently." He said no negligence will be tolerated. Talking about the government's stance in preventing religious extremism, the state minister said, "The people of the country have given a verdict against militancy and therefore, the government will control extremism with marked stringency." Referring to police reforms, Sohel Taj, as he is better known, said reforms in police were necessary. "Unless the lifestyle of members of police undergoes positive changes, efforts to improve law and order will not be successful." Sohel Taj went to office on Thursday though it was a holiday. bdnews2
